<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">You're not bad with that wind glider. Your gliding style seems familiar...</font>

244
00:30:22,100 --> 00:30:23,000
<b>Pasichnik:</b> How'd you get your eyepatch?

245
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:25,950
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">My eye patch? Wanna hear my story, eh?</font>

246
00:30:25,950 --> 00:30:30,850
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">I didn't have time to introduce properly... Well, it wasn't on my mind to begin with.</font>

247
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:37,950
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Ehe... My apologies. I'm Kaeya, Cavalry Captain for the Knights of Favonius.</font>

248
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:40,000
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">We can talk more after we get things sorted.</font>

249
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:43,500
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">I know a great place more for a chat.</font>

250
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:48,600
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">You're not bad with that wind glider. Your gliding style seems familiar...</font>

251
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:49,500
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Why is Jean the Acting Grand Master?

252
00:30:49,500 --> 00:30:54,540
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">The Grand Master is currently off leadingan expedition, so the Master, Jean, has stepped in to oversee the Knights while he's gone</font>

253
00:30:55,000 --> 00:31:00,000
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Hence, you'll hear refer to her as the Acting Grand Master.</font>

254
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:07,950
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">When the Grand Master left, he took the vast majority of our knights with him, leaving the Acting Grand Master with far more responsibility and stress.</font>

255
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:11,750
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Come to think of it, it must have been difficult for jean.</font>

256
00:31:15,450 --> 00:31:17,000
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">I'm Lisa, the librarian. Do you need anything, cutie?</font>

257
00:31:16,250 --> 00:31:17,000
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Id like to know more about monsters.

258
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:21,850
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">The monsters out in the wild? We've got many resources here in the library.</font>

259
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:27,400
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Making good use of elemental advanteges is the key to winning any battle.</font>

260
00:31:27,450 --> 00:31:32,350
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">By the way, would you be interested in having a part-time job here?</font>

261
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:37,950
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">We need people to... need people for doing... We just need more people.</font>

262
00:31:40,900 --> 00:31:42,200
<b>Pasichnik:</b> How do we fight Stormterror?

263
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:45,550
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">A way to fight against Stormterror...</font>

264
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:49,350
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">I'm sorry, but there's no way to do it alone.</font>

265
00:31:49,400 --> 00:31:55,350
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Judging by the level of its Anemo power, it's definetly not an ordinary creature.</font>

266
00:31:55,400 --> 00:32:00,600
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">I could teach you some elemental basics, so you'll have an idea of what I'm talking about.</font>

267
00:32:04,500 --> 00:32:06,850
<b><font color="beige">Jean:</font></b> <font color="beige">Thank you for accepting our invitation, traveler.</font>

268
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:06,850
<b>Pasichnik:</b> How do we fight Stormterror?

269
00:32:06,900 --> 00:32:10,750
<b><font color="beige">Jean:</font></b> <font color="beige">Its change in size and power really is suspicious.</font>

270
00:32:10,850 --> 00:32:15,750
<b><font color="beige">Jean:</font></b> <font color="beige">But for the Knights of Favonius, our priority is to deal with the aftermath of this attack.</font>

271
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:22,200
<b><font color="beige">Jean:</font></b> <font color="beige">The Gramd Master entrusted the Knights of Favonius to me. I cannot let him or the people of Mondstadt down.</font>

272
00:32:22,250 --> 00:32:24,550
<b><font color="beige">Jean:</font></b> <font color="beige">I must get to the buttom of this...</font>

273
00:32:27,500 --> 00:32:28,850
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Are all of the khights as... "strict" as Amber?

274
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:33,000
<b><font color="beige">Jean:</font></b> <font color="beige">I heard you and Outrider Amber had a misunderstanding.</font>

275
00:32:33,050 --> 00:32:36,100
<b><font color="beige">Jean:</font></b> <font color="beige">Please forgive her. She was just doing her job.</font>

276
00:32:36,200 --> 00:32:40,800
<b><font color="beige">Jean:</font></b> <font color="beige">Talk to Amber sometime. I'm sure you'll like how energetic she always is.</font>

277
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:51,600
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Wanna team up with me? Huh, I should warn you though, I don't slow down for anyone, greenhorn or otherwise.</font>

278
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:51,600
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Jean seems to be pretty reliable.

279
00:32:51,700 --> 00:32:58,000
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">With Jean by our side, nothing can stand in our way! ...At least, that's what I wanna say...</font>

280
00:32:58,050 --> 00:33:01,700
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">But I can't keep spouting that same old line.</font>

281
00:33:01,750 --> 00:33:08,000
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">She always dashes headlong into the heat of the battle, and we whant her to take better care of herself.</font>

282
00:33:08,050 --> 00:33:16,450
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">I really hope taht one day I can look Jean in the eye and tell her she doesn't need to worry anymore, because we have her back...</font>

283
00:33:18,650 --> 00:33:25,750
<b>Pasichnik:</b> You seem pretty good with a wind glider.

284
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:31,950
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">As a novice within the Knights of Favonius, your understanding of the wind is absolutely crucial.</font>

285
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:34,000
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Leave the advanced wind glider training to me!</font>

286
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:55,550
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>From now on, the adventures will probably get more and more dangerous. We should make sure we're prepared.</i>

287
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:58,550
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>We could start by going to Mondstadt's blacksmith.</i>

288
00:34:58,600 --> 00:35:00,250
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>There's the blacksmith!</i>

289
00:35:07,100 --> 00:35:09,350
<b>Wagner - Blacksmith:</b> What?

290
00:35:07,250 --> 00:35:09,350
<b>Pasichnik:</b> I'm looking for a weapon.

300
00:35:09,400 --> 00:35:15,350
<b>Wagner - Blacksmith:</b> Over there. Take your pick. Or, if you need something else I can make it on request.

301
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:19,000
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Wow, he does bespoke weaponry...</i>

302
00:35:19,050 --> 00:35:26,650
<b>Wagner - Blacksmith:</b> Of course. I sell weapons, make them to order, and do refinements. All in the job description for a blacksmith.

303
00:35:26,700 --> 00:35:33,100
<b>Wagner - Blacksmith:</b> All you need is the ore.

304
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:33,100
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Do you sell it here?

305
00:35:33,150 --> 00:35:38,050
<b>Wagner - Blacksmith:</b> No. Buy from someone else, I barely have enough for myself.

306
00:35:38,100 --> 00:35:44,250
<b>Wagner - Blacksmith:</b> You look confused. Listen, I'll tell you where the nearest deposit are.

307
00:35:44,300 --> 00:35:49,650
<b>Wagner - Blacksmith:</b> Bring some back and I'll help you forge what you need.

308
00:35:45,750 --> 00:35:49,650
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Great. Thanks!

309
00:35:49,700 --> 00:35:52,500
<b>Wagner - Blacksmith:</b> No need. I have other things to do.

310
00:35:54,500 --> 00:35:59,000
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>He seems like a short-tempered guy... Was it something we said?</i>

311
00:36:48,200 --> 00:36:52,050
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">This is it. One of the deserted <b>temples of The Four Winds</b>.</font>

312
00:36:52,100 --> 00:36:58,400
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">This temples have been left to waste for years now. The people of Mondstadt almost never come here.</font>

313
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:02,500
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">There's a chance there's a monster nest or a hilichurl camp inside.</font>

314
00:37:02,550 --> 00:37:09,850
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Even Stormterror has geven up on its own temple.</font>

315
00:37:03,950 --> 00:37:09,850
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Stormterror..?

316
00:37:09,900 --> 00:37:12,000
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">...Yes.</font>

317
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:19,100
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">I also find it hard to accept, but... Stormterror was once one of The Four Winds.</font>

318
00:37:19,350 --> 00:37:21,650
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Ehhhh!?</i>

319
00:37:21,700 --> 00:37:26,750
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Wait... Did you just feel that?</font>

320
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:29,300
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">The wind here... Something off...</font>

321
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:34,700
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Let's go in and look, Pasichnik. Be careful, the dragon's power is disturbing this area.</font>

322
00:37:58,000 --> 00:37:59,850
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">You can use that console to open the door.</font>

323
00:38:04,500 --> 00:38:06,800
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Wow! I can see so far in the temple!</font>

324
00:39:03,500 --> 00:39:05,200
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Oh no! A horn!</font>

325
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:08,200
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">The fighting must have got them riled up.</font>

326
00:39:09,750 --> 00:39:14,450
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Wellm good thing I've prepared my secret weapon: <b>Explosive Puppet "Baron Bunny"</b>!</font>

327
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:54,750
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Are those <b>explosive barrels</b> over there?</font>

328
00:39:56,200 --> 00:39:58,650
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Well... One shot should be able to blow them up!</font>

329
00:40:33,950 --> 00:40:36,750
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">It's so high... Seems like there's something up there.</font>

330
00:40:38,150 --> 00:40:40,750
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>But how do we get across?</i>

331
00:40:41,850 --> 00:40:44,800
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Isn't this... a Pyro Monument?</i>

332
00:40:46,500 --> 00:40:50,350
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>If we hit it with a powerful Pyro attack, we might trigger it!</i>

333
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:23,500
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Dragon's breath! Is that where the power is coming from?</font>

334
00:41:25,150 --> 00:41:27,000
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Great, let's smash it!</font>

335
00:41:27,650 --> 00:41:30,100
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Phew, I'm tired.</font>

336
00:41:30,150 --> 00:41:34,750
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">But at least this way we've helped Jean out.</font>

337
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:40,300
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">In the past, we were at least able to defend the city and keep it safe.</font>

338
00:41:40,300 --> 00:41:46,450
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">This, of course, is mostly thanks to Jean.</font>

339
00:41:46,500 --> 00:41:54,550
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">But now with Stormterror directly attacking the city itself...</font>

340
00:41:54,650 --> 00:42:00,850
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">"The winds change, so too should our tactics."</font>

341
00:41:57,650 --> 00:42:00,850
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Sounds deep.

342
00:42:00,900 --> 00:42:03,150
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">It's what Lisa like to say.</font>

343
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:07,350
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Speaking of which, The Four Winds we were discussing earlier...</font>

345
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:10,950
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">If you want to learn more about our history, you can ask Lisa.</font>

346
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:14,550
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">...I'm not saying I don't know our history! It's just...</font>

347
00:42:14,600 --> 00:42:21,600
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">I mean... A librarian is supposed to be more knowledgeable than an Outrider, right?</font>

348
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:30,000
(Пасічник - їбав я у рота твої крутки перекладати!)

349
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:06,000
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">You've arrived.</font>

350
00:46:06,050 --> 00:46:09,650
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Come closer. Can you smell that?</font>

351
00:46:07,100 --> 00:46:09,650
<b>Pasichnik:</b> It's the smell of burnt Pyro Slimes.

352
00:46:09,700 --> 00:46:11,950
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Something must be happend in the <b>temple</b>.</font>

353
00:46:12,000 --> 00:46:17,800
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">I imagine there will be slimes, hilichurls, and... whatewer is giving Stormterror extra power.</font>

354
00:46:17,850 --> 00:46:22,450
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Oh yes, it is going to be lively in there indeed!</font>

355
00:46:19,350 --> 00:46:22,450
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Will it be dangerous?

356
00:46:22,500 --> 00:46:28,050
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">As bustling as it may be - no, I can't imagine it will be dangerous at all.</font>

357
00:46:28,100 --> 00:46:32,450
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">It's a pity that the Temple of the Wolf has been disturbed by such an atrocity.</font>

358
00:46:28,500 --> 00:46:34,600
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Let's head in, Pasichnik.</font>

359
00:46:34,650 --> 00:46:40,250
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">No one makes offerings to The Four Winds anymore, yet the old winds never vanish...</font>

360
00:46:40,300 --> 00:46:44,400
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">We need to clear out the temples, for The Four Winds.</font>

361
00:47:10,600 --> 00:47:14,750
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Let me show ypu how the Knights of Favonius conquer our adversaries!</font>

362
00:47:23,500 --> 00:47:27,600
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Hmm. If I'm not mistaken, the end of the templeshould be up there.</font>

363
00:47:28,850 --> 00:47:30,350
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Wait... How do you know?</i>

364
00:47:31,450 --> 00:47:33,450
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Heh, experience.</font>

365
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:41,350
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">The kind of experience you get after years of dealing with things like this for others.</font>

366
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:45,750
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Dodge this!</font>

367
00:47:51,700 --> 00:47:52,850
<b><font color="darkred">Noel:</font></b> <font color="darkred">Leave it all to me.</font>

368
00:47:57,250 --> 00:48:01,850
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Traveler... Unless I'm mistaken, you don't seem to have a Vision.</font>

369
00:48:03,350 --> 00:48:07,000
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">So how exactly is it that you're able to channel elemental energy?</font>

370
00:48:08,650 --> 00:48:11,000
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>It was a very strange occurance.</i>

371
00:48:22,650 --> 00:48:23,750
<b><font color="darkred">Noel:</font></b> <font color="darkred">Someone needs assistents.</font>

372
00:48:58,500 --> 00:48:59,300
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Cooling!</font>

373
00:49:22,650 --> 00:49:25,000
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Ugh, finaly... we're here.</i>

374
00:49:26,450 --> 00:49:30,000
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Seems the path ends here. Let's use the <b>wind currents</b> to fly up.</font>

375
00:50:07,750 --> 00:50:10,000
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Whater! We can use this to put out fire!</i>

376
00:50:11,350 --> 00:50:13,800
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Good idea. That's some keen observation.</font>

377
00:50:15,350 --> 00:50:17,850
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">We should get Jean to give you a title and make you a knight.</font>

378
00:50:24,150 --> 00:50:25,000
<b><font color="darkred">Noel:</font></b> <font color="darkred">I'll catch up.</font>

379
00:50:58,000 --> 00:50:59,450
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Speaking of, did you know?</font>

380
00:51:00,950 --> 00:51:03,350
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Stormterror was once one of The Four Winds.</font>

381
00:51:04,900 --> 00:51:10,150
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">I'm not aware of the exact details. If you're interested, you can ask Acting Grand Master about it.</font>

382
00:51:20,150 --> 00:51:22,850
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Is that the thing that Stormterror is using to gain its power?</i>

383
00:51:24,400 --> 00:51:26,450
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Seems probable. Let's deal with it.</font>

384
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:36,700
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Bravo! What a performance!</font>

385
00:51:36,800 --> 00:51:40,200
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">You are, to my surprise, a well-trained knight.</font>

386
00:51:40,250 --> 00:51:45,350
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">The battles you just fought were sights to behold.</font>

387
00:51:42,000 --> 00:51:45,350
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Thanks, that's nice of you to say...

388
00:51:45,400 --> 00:51:50,300
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Haha. I see you already have the knightly virtue of modesty.</font>

389
00:51:50,400 --> 00:51:58,200
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Stories of your heroic deeds to save Mondstadt from destruction shall be known throughot the City of Freedom, well into the future.</font>

390
00:51:58,250 --> 00:52:01,450
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Please do visit me at our headquaters when you have the time.</font>

391
00:52:01,500 --> 00:52:05,600
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">I also know a lovely tavern, if that's more your thing.</font>

392
00:52:07,450 --> 00:52:09,850
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Quite rewarding, no?</font>

393
00:52:10,350 --> 00:52:12,850
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>We've seized another temple from Stormterror's grasp!</i>

394
00:52:13,950 --> 00:52:18,950
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">I can take care of the rest here. You go take care of other things while I'm at it.</font>

395
00:52:19,950 --> 00:52:21,300
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>See you later then, bye-bye~!</i>

396
00:52:23,550 --> 00:52:29,500
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">There's no way hilichurls organized an ambush like this themselves - not with their limited mental capacity...</font>

397
00:52:34,500 --> 00:52:36,150
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Thus YOU were behind this.</font>

398
00:52:40,000 --> 00:52:42,850
<font color="steelblue">Гогус, Чізо Вонф</font>

399
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:03,350
<font color="firebrick">Knights of Favonius... Always so inefficient.</font>

400
00:53:03,800 --> 00:53:11,000
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Agree to dissagree. But, your involment in this just made things a whole more interesting.</font>

401
00:53:17,900 --> 00:53:23,700
Obtained New Character
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya</font></b>

402
00:54:24,450 --> 00:54:25,850
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Our reward on the road.

403
00:56:02,850 --> 00:56:04,850
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Hey cutie.</font>

404
00:56:04,950 --> 00:56:09,000
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">You're going to help me out too? How kind of you.</font>

405
00:56:09,050 --> 00:56:12,900
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Don't hesitate to come to me if you need anything.</font>

406
00:56:10,050 --> 00:56:12,900
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Why would a librarian be at the ruins...?

407
00:56:12,950 --> 00:56:15,500
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Hmm... Good question.</font>

408
00:56:15,550 --> 00:56:18,750
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Well, because Jean trusts me.</font>

409
00:56:18,850 --> 00:56:21,200
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">So you should as well.</font>

410
00:56:50,400 --> 00:56:52,830
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">I guess I could give this a go.</font>

411
00:56:58,050 --> 00:57:02,500
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">I knew it. There is a strong elemental energy coming from deep within this temple.</font>

412
00:57:03,750 --> 00:57:05.800
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Paimon, are you able to float across?</font>

413
00:57:07,000 --> 00:57:08,800
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Can't do much even if she does.</i>

414
00:57:11,550 --> 00:57:13,500
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Let's ride this wind current, shall we?</font>

415
00:57:49,650 --> 00:57:50,450
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Leave it to me.</font>

416
00:57:54,450 --> 00:57:56,250
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">You're in for a little shock.</font>

417
00:58:01,500 --> 00:58:05,000
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Hey, a chest! How do we reach it...</i>

418
00:58:06,950 --> 00:58:08,500
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">It's an Electro Monument.</font>

419
00:58:09,800 --> 00:58:15,700
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">No wonder. Let me try to activate it with a bit of Electro power. Stand back, sweeties.</font>

420
00:58:26,600 --> 00:58:29,450
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Come a little closer... Hm-he-he</font>

421
00:58:54,350 --> 00:58:55,430
<b>Pasichnik:</b> With the wind!

422
00:58:57,100 --> 00:58:58,950
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">You're in for a little shock.</font>

423
00:58:59,900 --> 00:59:02,500
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">When it comes to Wet enemies, I've got them covered.</font>

424
00:59:21,300 --> 00:59:24,630
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Oh, another wind current. Let's ride it up from here.</font>

425
00:59:44,250 --> 00:59:46,050
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">No one escape my sights.</font>

426
00:59:51,700 --> 00:59:54,400
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Come a little closer... Blitz!</font>

427
01:00:06,850 --> 01:00:08,100
<b><font color="blue">Kaeya:</font></b> <font color="blue">Dodge this!</font>

428
01:00:08,350 --> 01:00:09.650
<b><font color="red">Amber:</font></b> <font color="red">Go-go Barron Bunny!</font>

429
01:00:12,200 --> 01:00:15,450
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Chain lightning can be set off between Electro-Charged opponents.</font>

430
01:00:16,730 --> 01:00:19,250
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">The electrical discharge caused by friction is only a little less shocking than love at first sight.</font>

431
01:00:21,200 --> 01:00:23,560
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Oh, you want to know about this gem?</font>

432
01:00:24,860 --> 01:00:28,900
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">You're kidding... You're seriously asking? This is a Vision.</font>

433
01:00:30,250 --> 01:00:33,000
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">It's used by the chosen to draw on elemental powers.</font>

434
01:00:34,500 --> 01:00:38,630
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">In terms of mysticism, I suppose you could call it a "magical lightning rod".</font>

435
01:00:49,220 --> 01:00:53,750
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">What... You've never see a Vision? Just where exactly are you from...?</font>

436
01:00:54,450 --> 01:00:57,850
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Are you a hilichurl with some level of reasonable intelligence?</font>

437
01:00:59,200 --> 01:01:04,650
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">No. I doubt it. After all, hilichurls aren't exactly known for their smarts.</font>

438
01:01:05,950 --> 01:01:09,830
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">And you, you'd more or less qualify to be a magister's apprentice.</font>

439
01:01:16,150 --> 01:01:18,300
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Break it and we can go head home and relax.</font>

440
01:01:19,650 --> 01:01:23,660
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">The thought of putting my feet up and relaxing has me all fired up!</font>

441
01:01:26,650 --> 01:01:30,760
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Oh, it's one of those consolidated wind thingies...</i>

442
01:01:30,860 --> 01:01:33,000
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Pasichnik, let's head back to the Statue of The Seven at Windrise and offer it to the gods!</i>

443
01:01:34,200 --> 01:01:40,050
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Dragon of the East, Lion of the South, Wolf of the North, Falcon of the West...</font>

444
01:01:40,050 --> 01:01:45,760
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">They are the Four Winds of Mondstadt, affilated with Barbatos, the God of Anemo.</font>

445
01:01:45,770 --> 01:01:50,850
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">The Dragon of the East, Stormterror - its real name, is Dvalin.</font>

446
01:01:50,860 --> 01:01:55,900
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Though most in Mondstadt seem to have forgotten that in al this "Stormterror" buisness.</font>

447
01:01:55,930 --> 01:02:03,650
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">So now you know why Dvalin is only able to channel three of the Four Wind's power.</font>

448
01:02:03,660 --> 01:02:07,350
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Because it has been consuming itself from the begining.</font>

449
01:02:04,800 --> 01:02:07,350
<b>Pasichnik:</b> Why?

450
01:02:07,430 --> 01:02:09,700
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Because of hatred, I presume.</font>

451
01:02:09,900 --> 01:02:12,130
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>Hatred...?</i>

452
01:02:12,330 --> 01:02:14,000
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Hatred for Mondstadt.</font>

453
01:02:14,100 --> 01:02:20,630
<b><font color="purple">Lisa:</font></b> <font color="purple">Hatred drove it to become something more powerful than the wind itself - to become Stormterror.</font>

454
01:02:20,830 --> 01:02:23,400
<b>Paimon:</b> <i>But why would one of The Four Winds...</i>

